olive oil
1 Chorizo & Salchichon Pizza
1 cucumber
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 220°C/ 200°C fan-forced.
• Sprinkle diced bacon over chorizo & salchichon pizza.
• Place pizza directly on wire oven rack and bake until cheese is melted and golden, 12-15 minutes.

TIP: Placing the pizza directly onto the wire racks helps the base to crisp up.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop cucumber.
• When the pizza has 5 minutes remaining, combine mixed salad leaves, cucumber and balsamic & olive oil dressing in a medium bowl.

• Slice chorizo, bacon and salchichon pizza.
• Divide pizza between plates. Serve with balsamic cucumber salad. Enjoy!